<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 98-08-03 - Replacing Terminal Pins on the Single Engine Controller (ECM) Chassis Harness Connector
    </stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi980803" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>98-08-03</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>May, 1998</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>ELECTRICAL</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Replacing Terminal Pins on the Single Engine Controller (ECM) Chassis Harness Connector</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This TSI applies to all models with an International engine and Single Engine Controller (ECM).
                </para>
                <para>This procedure allows a technician to replace broken pins on the chassis harness, 60 pin, ECM
                    connector. This procedure is intended to be used only when one or two pins need replaced. When
                    replacement of a larger number of pins is required, harness replacement is recommended.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <partsinfo>
            <table id="t9808031" frame="all">
                <title>Parts Information</title>
                <tgroup cols="3" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                    <colspec colwidth="1.75in"/>
                    <colspec colwidth="2.75in"/>
                    <colspec colwidth="1.01in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Part Number</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Part Description</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Quantity</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>2501100C1</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>Terminal and Wire</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry valign="top" align="center">
                                <para>1</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The terminal and wire, Part Number 2501100C1, is included in Parts Kit ZTSE 4436.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </partsinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="4">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Failure to remove the negative battery cables and the ECM power connector from the batteries
                        in the battery box before working on the ECM connector could cause personal injury as well as
                        damage to truck components.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9808031">Figure 1</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f9808031" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9808031.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. KNOB SCREW</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. KNOB ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. WIRE DRESS COVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. LOCKING TABS</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. FOAM BLOCK</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove all of the negative battery cables and the ECM power connections from the
                    batteries in the battery box.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the chassis harness connector from the ECM.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove tape from the connector cover end.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the knob screw and the knob.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the wire dress cover (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9808031">Item 3, Figure 1</hotlnk>) by prying the four tabs and gently pulling the
                    cover from the connector body.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the RED secondary connector lock which retains the pin(s) to be replaced by
                    prying with a small screwdriver at the locations shown (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9808032">Figure 2</hotlnk>). This will allow access to the connector lock and the
                    pin.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9808032" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9808032.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Gently pry and hold the connector lock away from the pin (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9808033">Figure 3</hotlnk>). Pull the pin through the connector body from the back
                    side of the connector.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9808033" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9808033.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Figure 3.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Cut the wire leading to the damaged connector at a point where good wire is available.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Cut the wire on terminal butt splice 2501100C1 (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9808034">Figure 4</hotlnk>) to the appropriate length.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9808034" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9808034.webp" type="webp" resolution="300"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Splice the new terminal and wire to the old wire.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the repaired terminal and wire into the proper cavity until it clicks. The pin
                    should lock in place.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the secondary connector lock.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-assemble the connector cover and tightly wrap the end with two layers of tape.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-assemble the knob and tighten the knob screw to 5 in-lbs. of torque.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect the ECM connector and tighten to 35 in-lbs. of torque.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect all of the negative battery cables and the ECM power connections to the
                    batteries in the battery box.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </tsi>
